Business Brief -- Revco D.S. Inc.:
   Investment Group to Give
   Support to Reorganization
Zell/Chilmark's offer would provide $6.97 a share to
holders of Revco's subordinated notes and others who would
have received only common stock under the original proposal.
The proposal Zell/Chilmark supports, offered by Revco's
noteholders, unsecured trade creditors and certain lenders,
is backed by Revco and rivaled by reorganization plans
offered by Rite Aid Corp. and Jack Eckerd Corp.